claim.claim-text:
1. A method for operating a digital, programmable hearing aid, comprising: 
picking up an input signal with an input transducer; 
converting the input signal into an audio signal; 
processing and performing a frequency-dependent amplification of the audio signal with a signal processing unit; 
converting and outputting the audio signal with an output transducer; 
setting a maximum-amplification transmission characteristic of a maximum amplification of the audio signal over a frequency range; 
determining at least one amplification modification value in at least one frequency range from a parameter that can be set by at least one of a hearing aid user and a parameter that is automatically generated by the signal processing unit; and 
determining a final amplification value at a respective frequency for an initial amplification value, taking the amplification modification value into consideration, and the final amplification value being limited to a maximum gain to produce an effective system gain for the respective frequency.

7. The method according to claim 5, further comprising: 
processing signals in a plurality of parallel frequency channels of the signal processing unit; 
separately setting, in at least two of the frequency channels, a transmission characteristic selected from the group consisting of the maximum-amplification transmission characteristic and the normal-amplification transmission characteristic.

9. A digital, programmable hearing aid, comprising: 
an input transducer configured to pick up an input signal and convert it into an audio signal; 
a signal processing unit configured to process and perform a frequency dependent amplification of the audio signal; 
a memory configured to hold amplification values characterizing a maximum-amplification transmission characteristic of a maximum amplification of the audio signal over a frequency range, the memory being connected to the signal processing unit; and 
an output transducer configured to produce an output signal from an audio signal processed by the signal processing unit.

11. The digital, programmable hearing aid according to claim 9, further comprising: 
at least one volume control adjustable by a hearing aid user; 
a signal processing unit comprising algorithms configured to perform an operation selected from the group consisting of situation analysis, unwanted noise suppression and compression; and 
at least one roll-off logic unit configured to determine an effective system amplification for a respective frequency from: 
the normal amplification; 
the maximum amplification; 
parameters associated with a volume control setting; and 
parameters determined from the algorithms.
